[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'Imagine being able to take a single photo and&nbsp; magically turn it into a full 3D holographic&nbsp;&nbsp; soccer card with one click. This is now&nbsp; possible using fal workflows. In this video,&nbsp;&nbsp; I\'ll show you how to make your very own web&nbsp; app using this workflow from fal and Claude&nbsp;&nbsp; Code. We\'ll cover the entire process from&nbsp; scratch, including creating your own GitHub&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'repository and hosting it on Vercel. By the end&nbsp; of the video, we\'ll have created a web app that&nbsp;&nbsp; works on desktop and on mobile. that could be the&nbsp; start of your next business. Let\'s get started. So, this amazing workflow was created by the one&nbsp; and only Loves, who is an incredible creative&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'engineer here at fal and kind of famous online.&nbsp; In the beginning, you\'ll see it has a custom card&nbsp;&nbsp; opening pack animation with a little cut sign at&nbsp; the top. Incredible. And when you open the cards,&nbsp;&nbsp; a lot of them pop out and there\'s an autoscrolling&nbsp; feature and a bit of a kind of fake pseudo 3D&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[00:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'interaction. The whole thing is pretty magical&nbsp; looking. Now, the secret source code behind this&nbsp;&nbsp; web app is actually a fal workflow that we can&nbsp; check out by clicking on the workflow button.&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'fal workflows are a self-contained visual&nbsp; scripting environment where you have access&nbsp;&nbsp; to inputs from the user, different image and video&nbsp; models like you\'d expect from fal and some other&nbsp;&nbsp; really special tools that allow you to automate an&nbsp; entire sequence of events that give you a workflow&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[01:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'like the one we\'re going to use now. And the best&nbsp; part is that this workflow once it\'s created is&nbsp;&nbsp; available via API that we can use for a web app&nbsp; using cloud code or I guess regular programming&nbsp;&nbsp; too. So now let\'s create our very first prompt to&nbsp; get this web app started. And before we go into&nbsp;&nbsp;'

